{
  "texts": [
    "The potential of LLMs for text generation has led to investigations into their ability to produce clinical notes, with the aim of improving the efficiency of documentation of HCPs.",
    "As part of our efforts to incorporate LLM-powered CNG tools into real clinical workflows, we have focused on building trust on these tools by assessing the reliability of LLMs in performing CNG.",
    "Our observations indicate that LLMs do not consistently produce string-identical responses when aiming for semantically alike outputs, which are also aligned with annotations crafted by human experts.",
    "On multiple runs using the same prompt, we found that Meta's Llama 3.1 70B model was the most reliable, followed by Mistral's small model.",
    "Anthropic's Claude Haiku model outperformed OpenAI's ChatGPT 4o and 4o-mini models in terms of semantic consistency while the opposite was true for semantic similarity, but both proprietary models are subpar to Llama 3.1 70B and Mistral Small."
  ]
}